               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; groups of lines on the incipit page of the introduction and of each Gospel; incipits of all sections (one or two initial lines); section numbers; the word mǝˤǝraf "chapter"; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of the Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The "Golden Gospel" book of Qändaʿro Qǝddus Qirqos church.</note>
                     <note>- The canon tables are missing.</note>
                     <note>- The space left for the rubricated, initial lines of 'On the reliability of the Gospels' is unfilled (fol. 5va).</note>
                     <note>- No opening lines for the Gospel of Mark, the Gospel of Luke and the Gospel of John.</note>
                     <note>- The “tituli” of the Gospel of Matthew are only partly numbered (until “tituli” 15); the “tituli” of the Gospel of Mark and of the Gospel of Luke are not numbered; the numbers of the “tituli” of the Gospel of John are mistaken, after "10" follows 20 up to 29.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
