                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script">Very careful and regular. Written by trained hand.</ab>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid scarlet).</seg>The scribe who wrote Additiones 2 and 6 is Mänbärä Krǝstos.<date>Second half of 16th century?</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The handwriting remains very uniform throughout the Ms. with slender, tall and upright letters; tze script shows typical palaeographic features of the mid-16th until mid-17th cent. as well as a few archaic features.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
Characteristics:<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic">
- uniform shapes of the letters<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic">
- slender proportions and parallel downstrokes<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic">
- broadly spaced letters<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h8" script="Ethiopic">
- form of 'six' (፮, looking like "compressed" number 'seven') <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h9" script="Ethiopic">
- numeral 'ten' (፲) has a peculiar rare form with a ring on fol. 5vb (cp. Synaxarion of QDQ-004).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h10" script="Ethiopic">
- ው with marker of the 6th order closer to the top than in the middle <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h11" script="Ethiopic">
- መ and ሠ of smaller size than other characters, but written in the upper limit of the line<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h12" script="Ethiopic">
- the loops of መ are mostly separate in all vowel orders<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h13" script="Ethiopic">
- ጥ written with short curves<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h14" script="Ethiopic">
- tendency to keep open vocalization loops of the 5th order.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
