                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#6v">Fol. 6v</locus>: Record concerning a reconciliation agreement.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in Amharic. The reconciliation took place on 23 Mäskäräm 1889 A.M. (= 3 October 3 1934 A.D.); the document is sealed with fingerprints.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#43v">Fol. 43v</locus>: Excerpt from Mäṣḥafä gǝbrä ḥǝmamat "Book of the Rite of the Holy Week" (reading for Monday).<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 43v: በስሙነ: ሕማማት፡ ዝንቱ፡ ለከሃይል፡ ክብር፡ ወስብሐት፡ ወእዘዝ፡ እስከ፡ ለአለም፡ ... </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in the upper margin in the same hand as Additio 6.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#47vb">Fol. 47vb</locus>: Reconciliation note.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in Amharic.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#117ra">Fol. 117ra</locus>-va: Excerpt from the Ṣoma dǝggwa, Antiphonary for Lent (zä-ʿarb zä-sǝqlät). <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 117ra: ዘንዋም፡ ተሰቅለ፡ ወሐመ፡ እንበለ፡ ኃጢአት፡ ተረግዘ፡ ገቦሁ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ደዊ፡ እስመ፡ መለኮቱ፡ ኢሐመ፡ ተሰቅለ፡ ከመ፡ ዕቡሰ፡ ማዕከለ፡ ፪ፈያት፡ ...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in the same hand in small script as the short excerpts at the end of each gospel (see: Other Details), with musical notation.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#117va">Fol. 117va-118</locus>ra: Record concerning the rules for the association (maḫbär) of Qändaʿro Qǝddus Qirqos (e.g., administration of land, periods of service of priests and deacons, wages). <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in Amharic in a crude hand. Two short notes were added at the end amending the rules, in pen.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#148ra">Fol. 148ra</locus>: Signature of the scribe, exhortation.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 148ra: ዘጸሐፊሂ፡ መንበረ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ኢትርስኡኒ፡ በጸሎትክሙ፡ ፩፡ አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 148ra: Do not forget me, the scribe Mänbärä Krǝstos, in your prayer (recite for me) the Pater Noster one (time).</q>
                           Written in the upper margin in the same hand as Additio 2.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The introduction and the special introductions to each Gospel (biographies and lists of “tituli”) are written in small script.&#xD;
- Short excerpts from the Ṣoma dǝggwa (Antiphonary for Lent) with musical notation for Good Friday at the end of each Gospel are written (in the same hand as Additio 5) in the upper margin of fols. 44ra-46ra, 71ra-71vb, 113ra-115ra and 146vb-148ra; these fols. contain also remarks in the side margins/intercolumn indicating an assigned reading at a certain time of a day; additional notes on these fols. were erased.&#xD;
- Several short remarks are written interlineally or in the margins, in pen or ink, e.g.,&#xD;
concerning St. Qirqos:  fols. 21va, 30rb, 31vb;&#xD;
the feast of Däbrä Tabor: fols. 29rb, 60ra. &#xD;
the feast of Däbrä Zäyt: fol. 38va. &#xD;
- A few corrections written over erased words and passages: e.g., fols. 2vb, 3ra, 71rb.&#xD;
- A few erasures: fols. 2rb, 2vb, 3va, 4va, 8r, 61va, 151rb [4 lines].&#xD;
- Pen trial: fol.  40v&#xD;
- A few words crudely written in pen: e.g., fols. 11r, 20r, 31v, 33v, 110r.</item>
                     </list>
